6.00	Stole_(song)	Stole (song)	"Stole" is a song by American singer Kelly Rowland. It was written and co-produced by Dane Deviller, Sean Hosein and Steve Kipner and recorded for Rowland's solo album Simply Deep (2002). Generally well-received by music critics, the lyrics of the track chronicle three different scenarios with young people, whose lives are drastically changed by the aftermaths of a suicide and a school shooting.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b9/Kellyrowland_stole.jpg/220px-Kellyrowland_stole.jpg
